OL,3,CTeenagers to be offered military gap
OL,4,Cyears to boost UK's defence
OL,6,FThe UK is set to offer young people
OL,7,Fpaid gap years with the armed forces,
OL,8,Fin a step towards a new "whole of
OL,9,Fsociety" approach to defence.
OL,11,FAround 150 young people will be
OL,12,Frecruited for placements of up to two
OL,13,Fyears, with the scheme expanding to
OL,14,Fmore than 1,000 per year, according to
OL,15,Fthe i paper.
OL,17,FThe scheme is due to open from March
OL,18,F2026, and is intended to introduce
OL,19,Fmore people to military life, or
OL,20,Fprovide transferable skills if they
OL,21,Fdecide not to enlist afterwards.
